<p>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>f</i>=E2=80=89(<i>x</i>)</span> is given b=
y a convergent power series in an open disk centred at <span class=3D"texht=
ml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> in the complex plane (or an =
interval in the real line), it is said to be <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Analytic_function" title=3D"Analytic function">analytic</a> in t=
his region.  Thus for <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">x</span> in this region, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-st=
yle:italic;">f</span> is given by a convergent power series<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-FOOTNOTESilverman1974[httpsbooksgooglecombooksidLIXBHcUrx-cCpgPA139_139=
]_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor=
