<p>The <i>error</i> incurred in approximating a function by its <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>th-degree Taylor pol=
ynomial is called the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Residual_(nu=
merical_analysis)" title=3D"Residual (numerical analysis)">remainder</a> an=
d is denoted by the function <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i><sub><i>n</i><=
/sub>(<i>x</i>)</span>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor%27s=
_theorem" title=3D"Taylor's theorem">Taylor's theorem</a> can be used to ob=
tain a bound on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor%27s_the=
orem#Explicit_formulas_for_the_remainder" title=3D"Taylor's theorem">size o=
f the remainder</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEKnapp2000[httpbooksgoogleco=
mbooksidDLfxd7StGw8CpgPA43_43=E2=80=9344]_15-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_series#cite_note-FOOTNOTEKnapp2000=
[httpbooksgooglecombooksidDLfxd7StGw8CpgPA43_43%E2%80%9344]-15"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In general, Taylor series need not be <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Convergent_series" title=3D"Convergent series">convergent</a> at=
 all. In fact, the set of functions with a convergent Taylor series is a <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meager_set" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Meager set">meager set</a> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Fr%C3%A9chet_space" title=3D"Fr=C3=A9chet space">Fr=C3=A9chet space<=
/a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smooth_functions" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Smooth functions">smooth functions</a>. Even if the T=
aylor series of a function <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">f</span> does converge, its limit need not be equal to the value =
of the function <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>f</i>=E2=80=89(<i>x</i>)</span>.=
 For example, the function
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
