      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \ln(1+x)=3Dx-=
{\frac {x^{2}}{2}}+{\frac {x^{3}}{3}}+O{\left(x^{4}\right)}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2ff250ae7c05cb3a9bed0177c388ce9eba37babc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:34.758ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
ln(1+x)=3Dx-{\frac {x^{2}}{2}}+{\frac {x^{3}}{3}}+O{\left(x^{4}\right)}}"><=
/span>
and for the cosine function
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \cos x-1=3D-{\frac {x^{2}}{2}}+{\frac {x^{4}}{24}}-{\frac {x^{6=
}}{720}}+O{\left(x^{8}\right)}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>cos</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
